t can launch a four year quest to build rigid and fluid networks at the molecular level that can be applied in products as wide ranging as LCDs and pharmaceuticals  After all  chemistry at VMI  chemistry in Timmons  classroom and lab  is about students creating  new science   At VMI we get the students involved in answering real questions  said Timmons  That process means connecting the classroom with the lab  Teaching and learning in Timmons  classroom is an interactive process that begins with cadets and their professor putting their heads together   scheming  as Timmons calls it  The cadets then carry out the plan in the lab and report their findings   The fun part about research is that molecules often don t do what we want them to do  said Timmons   We re always trying to make our molecules behave  We add a solvent or vary a connecting unit   Our students in the lab seeing the connection between what they learn from a book and what s really out there  That connection extends even further as Timmons procures grants for materials for real research culminating in published articles with cadets among the authors   If I can get a student interested in a problem  then they re willing to sort out the difficulties  said Timmons  The chemistry lab at VMI offers a chance for cadets to couple their creativity with the discipline of Institute life  There  Timmons said   We build some beautiful molecules   If I can get a student interested in a problem  then they re willing to sort out the difficulties  Col  Daren Timmons Professor and Department Head  Chemistry John C  Allen  62 Institute Professorship in Chemistry Ph D  Texas A M University Specialty  Inorganic chemistry   Share this entry Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on Google  Share on Linkedin Share on Tumblr Share on Reddit Share by Mail Stories   Videos Stories   Video Home Stories Slideshows Day in the Life Video Library Admissions Video More About Life at VMI Cadets Academics Athletics Challenge Alumni 